# Connector config descriptors + the generated index are byte-deterministic artifacts (FX-CFG-001):
# pin them to LF so `build_connector_index` output matches the committed file on every OS (the
# validator's freshness check is byte-exact). Scoped narrowly — NOT a repo-wide renormalization.
connectors/index.json text eol=lf
connectors/*/config.json text eol=lf
connectors/_schema/*.json text eol=lf
connectors/*/SETUP.md text eol=lf

# Mod descriptors + generated index/SETUP (FX-MOD-CFG-001) — same byte-exact freshness contract,
# so pin them to LF too (the connector pinning above was not mirrored for mods initially; on a
# Windows checkout with autocrlf the mod validator's byte-exact check would otherwise false-fail —
# SG-2026-06-15-A). Scoped narrowly, not a repo-wide renormalization.
mods/index.json text eol=lf
mods/*/config.json text eol=lf
mods/_schema/*.json text eol=lf
mods/*/SETUP.md text eol=lf
